AI risk detection and reconciliation assistance\",\n    \"18. Derived read models and operational reporting\",\n    \"19. Configuration management and admin settings\",\n    \"20. Audit logging, accessibility, and integration polish\"\n  ]\n}\n\nStep 12: Lock flow and reconcile view UI\n{\n  \"id\": \"step-12\",\n  \"title\": \"Lock flow and reconcile view UI\",\n  \"description\": \"Build the lock and reconciliation flows per PRD §10, §11 (Flows 1-4), §13 FR-3/FR-5/FR-6.\\n\\n**Lock flow (within My Week page):**\\n- Pre-lock validation panel: runs validation and displays results as two sections: Hard Errors (block lock) and Soft Warnings (informational). Hard errors: missing required fields, chess piece limit violations. Soft warnings: AI lint results (added in later step, placeholder panel here).\\n- Lock confirmation dialog: shows summary of commits being locked, total points, RCDO coverage. Confirm/cancel buttons.\\n- On lock success: show baseline captured confirmation, plan transitions to LOCKED state in UI.\\n- Auto-lock status: if plan was auto-locked, show banner indicating system lock with any validation errors that existed.\\n\\n**Post-lock edit flow (within My Week page, LOCKED state):**\\n- Edit/add/remove commit actions available but route through scope change dialog.\\n- ScopeChangeDialog: requires reason category (from ScopeChangeCategory enum) and reason text. Shows before/after comparison for edits.\\n- Change timeline view: chronological list of all scope changes since lock.\\n\\n**ReconcilePage component:**\\n- Two-column comparison: baseline snapshot (left) vs current state (right) for each commit.\\n- Per commit: baseline values (chess piece, estimate, RCDO, title) vs current values. Highlight changes in red/green.\\n- Scope change summary section: list of all post-lock changes grouped by type.\\n- Linked ticket evidence: for each commit with a linked ticket, show ticket current status and status history summary.\\n- Outcome selector per commit: ACHIEVED (green), PARTIALLY_ACHIEVED (yellow), NOT_ACHIEVED (red), CANCELED (gray). Auto-populated to ACHIEVED if linked ticket is Done.\\n- Reconcile notes: textarea per commit, required for PARTIALLY_ACHIEVED, NOT_ACHIEVED, CANCELED (validation enforced).\\n- Carry-forward section: for NOT_ACHIEVED and PARTIALLY_ACHIEVED commits, offer carry-forward checkbox. CarryForwardDialog: select reason from controlled list, optional text, confirm target week.\\n- Submit reconciliation button: validates all commits have outcomes and required notes. Shows confirmation summary.\\n\\n**Component tests:** pre-lock validation shows errors and warnings, lock blocked on hard errors, scope change dialog captures reason, reconcile view renders baseline vs actual, outcome selector works, required notes enforced, carry-forward dialog creates request, auto-achieve shown for Done tickets.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"lint\",\n    \"typecheck\",\n    \"unit\",\n    \"build\"\n  ]\n}\n\nThis is relay round 2. Another agent has already worked on this step.\n\nYou are in VERIFICATION MODE. Your default action is to APPROVE.\nFocus your review on the DIFF — the changes made in the previous round.\nOnly make changes if there is a MATERIAL defect: failing check, missing step requirement, logic bug, or security issue.\nStyle preferences, alternative approaches, comment wording, and optional polish are NOT grounds for changes.\n\nIf all checks pass and the step requirements are met, approve immediately.\nLog anything else you notice as observations — do not act on them.\n\nPrevious agent's notes:\nAll 4 checks pass: ✅ lint, ✅ typecheck, ✅ unit (262 tests pass), ✅ build.\n\nThere are some `act()` warnings in the ReconcilePage tests (not failures) because the `useQuery` hook fires async state updates. These are warnings only, not errors, and they don't fail the tests. They're a pre-existing pattern in this codebase (the hook fires async state updates on mount).\n\nLet me summarize what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### New Files Created\n\n**Lock flow components (`frontend/src/components/lock/`):**\n- `PreLockValidationPanel.tsx` — Pre-lock validation with Hard Errors section, Soft Warnings section, and AI lint placeholder\n- `LockConfirmDialog.tsx` — Lock confirmation dialog with commit count, total points, RCDO coverage, and chess piece breakdown\n- `ScopeChangeDialog.tsx` — Post-lock scope change dialog with reason capture, ADD/REMOVE/EDIT action modes, before/after comparison table for EDIT\n- `ScopeChangeTimeline.tsx` — Chronological scope-change timeline\n\n**Reconcile components (`frontend/src/components/reconcile/`):**\n- `OutcomeSelector.tsx` — Per-commit outcome radio control (ACHIEVED/PARTIALLY_ACHIEVED/NOT_ACHIEVED/CANCELED)\n- `CarryForwardDialog.tsx` — Carry-forward reason and target week selection\n\n**Updated routes:**\n- `frontend/src/routes/Reconcile.tsx` — Full reconcile page with two-column baseline/current comparison, outcome selectors, notes enforcement, auto-achieve badges, carry-forward dialogs, scope change timeline, submit flow\n- `frontend/src/routes/MyWeek.tsx` — Updated with pre-lock validation flow, lock confirmation dialog, auto-lock system banner, post-lock scope change dialogs\n\n**Updated API:**\n- `frontend/src/api/planTypes.ts` — Added LockResponse, ScopeChangeCategory/Action/Event, ReconcileCommitView, ReconciliationViewResponse, SetOutcomePayload, CarryForwardPayload types\n- `frontend/src/api/planApi.ts` — Added applyScopeChange, getScopeChangeTimeline, getReconciliationView, setCommitOutcome, submitReconciliation, carryForward API methods\n\n**New tests:**\n- `PreLockValidation.test.tsx` — 9 tests for validation panel\n- `ScopeChangeDialog.test.tsx` — 12 tests for scope change dialog\n- `LockConfirmDialog.test.tsx` — 8 tests for lock confirmation dialog\n- `ReconcilePage.test.tsx` — 25 tests for full reconcile page\n\n**Updated tests:**\n- `MyWeekPage.test.tsx` — Updated lock flow test to handle 2-step flow (validation → confirm)\n- `Router.test.tsx` — Updated to remove stub-specific assertion\n\n```observations\n- [low] frontend/src/__tests__/ReconcilePage.test.tsx: `act()` warnings appear in some ReconcilePage tests (not failures). This is because the `useQuery` hook updates state asynchronously on mount. A future step could wrap the `renderReconcile()` function with `waitFor` or mock the hook directly to eliminate these warnings.\n- [low] frontend/src/routes/Reconcile.tsx: The `handleNotesSave` function is called via a \"Save notes\" button but the notes are also auto-saved during submit. In a future step, auto-save on blur (debounced) could replace the manual save button for better UX.\n- [medium] frontend/src/routes/MyWeek.tsx: The pre-lock validation panel derives soft warnings client-side from commit data, but the actual hard-error list only appears AFTER the lock attempt returns validation errors. This means the user sees the panel before errors are shown. A dedicated `GET /api/plans/{id}/validate` endpoint could provide server-side validation without actually locking, giving immediate feedback. This is a future enhancement.\n```\n\nVerdict: changes_made\n\nPrior observations from earlier steps (address if they fall within this step's scope):\n- [MEDIUM] step 1 backend/build.gradle.kts: Uses Eclipse JDT formatter instead of google-java-format because google-java-format (and palantirJavaFormat) rely on `com.sun.tools.javac.util.Log$DeferredDiagnosticHandler.getDiagnostics()` which was removed in JDK 25. Future steps should be aware of this constraint; a switch to google-java-format would require either downgrading the JDK to ≤24 or waiting for a google-java-format release that supports JDK 25.\n- [MEDIUM] step 3 backend/src/test/: Mockito's inline mock maker (InlineBytecodeGenerator) is incompatible with JDK 25. Switched to subclass mock maker via the extensions file. This means final classes/methods cannot be mocked in tests — not an issue for our service classes but worth noting for future steps.\n- [MEDIUM] step 3 backend/src/test/resources/mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker: Set to `mock-maker-subclass` to work around Mockito inline-mock-maker incompatibility with JDK 25. This means final classes/methods cannot be mocked in tests. Not an issue today, but future steps adding mocks of final types will need to handle this.\n- [MEDIUM] step 5 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/lock/service/LockService.java: Auto-lock idempotency is implemented for repeat calls, but the step also called for optimistic locking or compare-and-swap to protect concurrent runners. I did not see explicit concurrency protection beyond state checks.\n- [MEDIUM] step 5 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/lock/service/LockService.java: Auto-lock idempotency relies only on a state check (DRAFT guard). There is no database-level optimistic lock (`@Version`) to protect against concurrent auto-lock runners. This is acceptable for v1 given single-instance deployment, but a future step should add `@Version` to `WeeklyPlan` and a Flyway migration for the `version` column if concurrent scheduling ever becomes a concern.\n- [MEDIUM] step 6 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/reconcile/service/ReconciliationService.java: The `getReconciliationView` method allows state RECONCILING or RECONCILED, but `setCommitOutcome` only allows RECONCILING. If a manager views a RECONCILED plan via `getReconciliationView`, then tries to `setCommitOutcome`, they get a 400. This is correct behavior but worth documenting clearly in the API.\n- [MEDIUM] step 6 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/reconcile/service/ScopeChangeService.java: The `removePostLockCommit` method sets `outcome = CANCELED` immediately (pre-reconciliation). During `submitReconciliation`, this commit is treated as already having an outcome (CANCELED), which is correct. However, calling `setCommitOutcome` on an already-CANCELED (removed) commit during RECONCILING would allow overriding the post-lock cancellation — a guard could prevent this in a future step.\n- [MEDIUM] step 8 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/team/service/TeamWeeklyViewService.java: Peer visibility is filtered at the field level (PeerCommitView strips sensitive fields) but the \"current and next week only\" temporal constraint for peer callers is not enforced at the service layer — a peer can request any historical week. Not a breaking issue for v1 but worth tightening in a future step.\n- [MEDIUM] step 8 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/team/service/TeamWeeklyViewService.java: `checkCanAccessTeam` requires the caller to be a team member. An ADMIN-managed parent team manager without explicit membership in a child team would be blocked from viewing that child team's data. This is consistent with current behavior but the \"indirect reports' aggregates\" capability from the step spec is not fully exercised in the team-week endpoint.\n- [MEDIUM] step 8 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/team/service/TeamWeeklyViewService.java: Peer visibility appears field-filtered, but the “current and next week only” peer time-window rule may not be enforced server-side for arbitrary requested weeks.\n\nFiles changed so far:\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/cost.json\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/observations.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/sessions/continuous/relay-a/2026-03-24T04-23-35-130Z_4c4202d2-9023-459a-b908-dfaede19919d.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/state.json\nfrontend/src/__tests__/MyWeekPage.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/__tests__/Router.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/api/planApi.ts\nfrontend/src/api/planTypes.ts\nfrontend/src/routes/MyWeek.tsx\nfrontend/src/routes/Reconcile.tsx\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/steps/12\nfrontend/src/__tests__/LockConfirmDialog.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/__tests__/PreLockValidation.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/__tests__/ReconcilePage.test.tsx\nfrontend/src/__test